    feat: Replace MQTT control plane with embedded BGP

    Galactic's distribution path moves from the Python galactic-router
    service over MQTT to standard MP-BGP L3VPN with SRv6 service SIDs.
    Each agent now embeds a GoBGP speaker peering iBGP with one or more
    cluster route reflectors; the router service and its broker are
    removed entirely.

    Design rationale and decision log: PLAN-bgp-cutover.md.
    Component-level reference for the resulting system: AS-BUILT.md.

    Major changes:

    - VPC identifiers narrow from 48 to 32 bits so the BGP route
      distinguisher (RFC 4364 type 2) and route target extended community
      (RFC 5668) carry the full ID without truncation. Attachment IDs
      remain 16 bits.
    - The operator gains --pop-locator and --asn flags; reconciler writes
      serviceSID, routeTarget, and routeDistinguisher into
      VPCAttachment.status alongside the identifier.
    - VPCAttachmentSpec.Routes and the derived NAD terminations are
      removed; pod prefixes are the only thing advertised. Anything
      reachable beyond the pod is learned via BGP.
    - New agent packages: bgp (GoBGP wrapper, originate/withdraw/watch,
      tunnel-encap and prefix-sid encodings with a startup-time
      round-trip guard), cache (joined VPC + VPCAttachment informer),
      program (kernel egress with explicit hex/base62 boundary),
      reconciler (central event loop with pending/active/ingress/
      programmedKernel/receivedRoutes state), health (/healthz +
      /metrics), metrics (Prometheus gauges).
    - Deleted: pkg/proto/remote, internal/agent/srv6/{srv6.go,
      routeegress, neighborproxy}, internal/cni/route, the entire
      router/ Python service, the lab MQTT/router manifests, and the
      paho.mqtt.golang dependency.
    - Cluster-wide configuration (POP-locator, ASN, BGP encoding) flows
      to agents via the operator ConfigMap so wire format and authority
      cannot diverge per-node.

    Tests, lint, and code generation are clean. Reconciler ordering and
    teardown paths have unit coverage; the prefix-sid wire format has a
    round-trip regression guard against the pinned GoBGP version.

